 The interval 
\begin_inset Formula $a\leq x\leq b$
\end_inset

 is divided in to 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 sub-intervals, each of length 
\begin_inset Formula $h=(b-a)/n$
\end_inset

, and area of a sub-interval is approximated by
\begin_inset Formula \[
